<hl>
<seg id=1> Ding Hao became the first undergraduate brought up in Chinese orphanage </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Hangzhou, September 1st(reporter: Zhu Guoxian, trainee: Guan Zhuhui) Ding Hao, brought up in the Hangzhou Orphanage, has recently received a matriculation notice from Hangzhou University and has become a student of Philosophy and Social Science Department of the university. </seg>
<seg id=3> It has been determined that 19-year-old Dinghao is the first undergraduate student to have been brought up in a Chinese orphanage, since the establishment of PRC. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> "Upon receiving the matriculation notice, I really wanted to jump up," said Ding Hao, but he can not express his excitement with the single word "jump". </seg>
<seg id=5> The high fever made the 3 year old Ding Hao contracted serious infantile paralysis (poliomyelitis), and he was adopted by the orphanage in the same year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Ding Hao finished his elementary schooling at the orphanage, and afterwards entered a middle school nearby. </seg>
<seg id=7> At first he was sent to and from school by teachers at orphanage, and from the second grade on he lived in the school, and returns to orphanage every Saturday.  No matter how much wind or rain, he never missed a single class. </seg>
<seg id=8> He took part in the university entrance test and was accepted for matriculation at Hangzhou University this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> The success of Dinghao was the embodiment of efforts in all circles. </seg>
<seg id=10> The orphanage took good care of him for 16 years, and had spent over RMB3 thousand for tuition, materials, and other support since last year. </seg>
<seg id=11>  </seg>
<seg id=12> Upon learning of Dinghao's  matriculation, Hangzhou Longchang Grain and Oil Company donated RMB20 thousand to assist him in his study, and artificial limb factory provided him with a wheelchair, crutches, and other medical supplies. </seg>
</p>
